		<profileDesc>
			<abstract>
				<p>By adding a spatial regularization kernel to a standard loss function formulation of the boosting problem, we develop a framework for spatially informed boosting. From this regularized loss framework we derive an efficient boosting algorithm that uses additional weights/priors on the base classifiers. We prove that the proposed algorithm exhibits a &quot;grouping effect&quot;, which encourages the selection of all spatially local, discriminative base classifiers. The algorithm&apos;s primary advantage is in applications where the trained classifier is used to identify the spatial pattern of discriminative information, e.g. the voxel selection problem in fMRI. We demonstrate the algorithm&apos;s performance on various data sets.</p>
			</abstract>
